        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36129",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I see a small problem here:\r\nHow would you differentiate between \"my default value is {{NULL}}\" and \"please throw an exception if key is not found\"?\r\nMost likely that would require a third argument to {{Zend_Registry::get()}} - such as {{$throwOnNotFound}} or something like that.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-19T00:55:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-19T00:55:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36178",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=efreed",
                        "name": "efreed",
                        "displayName": "Eric Freed",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\r\nOption 1) (the assumed option requested by this issue) The user just doesn't get to use NULL, that's the price you pay for wanting a throw exception feature.  \r\nThis is very easily worked around by passing a blank string or a 0 and using that response.\r\n\r\nOption 2) Don't have the default be NULL, have it be something unusual like '__throw_exception__'\r\nThen you can compare to that fixed string and know if an exception should be thrown.\r\n\r\nOption 3) Don't define a second parameter and use func_get_arg(1)\r\nThis president has already been set with the isValid() method in Zend_Validate_Abstract\/Zend_Validate_Interface but is difficult to document.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=efreed",
                        "name": "efreed",
                        "displayName": "Eric Freed",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-19T11:16:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-19T11:16:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39428",
